    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so i'm buying a house in austin and things are moving fast. my agent said i need to put my earnest money into an escrow account, but i dont really get why i cant just hold onto it or pay the seller directly until the deal is done. why does a third party need to hold it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A third party holding your earnest money, or \"earnest money,\" is a necessary measure to keep things orderly. It's like a good-faith deposit, and holding it in escrow prevents a messy situation where one party might try to pull the rug out from under the other. If you don't have a neutral party, it's just a big pile of cash floating around, and that's a recipe for a real headache.",
